						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Sākshīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 3: 988 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of a silver pot weighing 143(3/4) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and 2 <hi rend="italic">mañjāḍi</hi> by Uḍaiyapirāṭṭiyār, the mother of Śrī-Uttamachōḷa for the merit of her son to the god at Tiruppuṟambiyam. It is further recorded that as per the weighing balance <hi rend="italic">(tilākkōl),</hi> called <hi rend="italic">turaiyakkali,</hi> the gifted vessel weighed 13 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and 1 <hi rend="italic">palam</hi> and as per the weighing stone of the <hi rend="italic">ūr,</hi> it weighed 140 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> 18 <hi rend="italic">mañjāḍi</hi> and 6 <hi rend="italic">mā.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
